     systems. In particular, solutions that sacrifice performance have been
     generally avoided. However, isolation techniques in modern languages can
     provide safety while avoiding performance issues. Moreover, utilizing a
     type-safe language with no garbage collector or other runtime services
     avoids what would otherwise be some of the largest sections of trusted
     code base. We report on our experiences in writing a resource efficient
